The paper focuses on the human-centered aspect of AI and how users develop mental models to understand AI systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of explainable AI, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also touches on the ethical implications of AI, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category. The use of cognitive tutoring methods suggests that the paper could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of AI approaches, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category.
